 operations.\n   - ControllerApis.scala handles controller-side request processing and similarly calls authHelper.authorize() for operations like CreateTopics, DeleteTopics, and AlterConfigs.\n   - AclApis.scala handles ACL management requests (CreateAcls, DeleteAcls, DescribeAcls) and authorizes these requests before processing them.\n\nThe audit logging flow is: Request Handler (KafkaApis/ControllerApis) -> AuthHelper.authorize() -> StandardAuthorizer.authorize() -> StandardAuthorizerData.authorize() -> logAuditMessage() which logs to the \"kafka.authorizer.logger\" with messages containing authorization status (Allowed/Denied) along with principal, operation, resource, and host information."
